This is a basic version of sentiment model.
In this model, attribute score and sentiment score all use wordembedding, but not lstm.
Use attribute labels to mask attribute loss and use attribute labels*sentiment labels to mask sentiment loss. This methods
can successfully process non-attribute situations, it can eliminate


Requirements:
attribute dim = word dim
sentiment dim = word dim
to make life easy, lstm_cell_size = word dim

seed = {'lstm_cell_size':30,
        'word_dim':30
       }
self.nn_config={'attributes_num':20,
                'attribute_senti_prototype_num':4,
                'normal_senti_prototype_num':4, # number of specific sentiment of each attribute
                'sentiment_dim':seed['attribute_dim'], # dim of a sentiment expression prototype.
                'attribute_dim':seed['word_dim'],
                'attribute_mat_size':3, # number of rows in attribute matrix
                'words_num':10,
                'word_dim':seed['word_dim'],
                'attribute_loss_theta':1.0,
                'sentiment_loss_theta':1.0,
                'is_mat':True,
                'epoch':None,
                'rps_num':5, # number of relative positions
                'rp_dim':15, # dimension of relative position
                'lr':0.003, # learing rate
                'batch_size':30,
                'lstm_cell_size':seed['lstm_cell_size'],
                'atr_threshold':0 # attribute score threshold
                }